# SaaS Boilerplate - Cursor Rules

## Architecture Rules

### File Size
- Maximum 300 lines per file
- If a file exceeds this limit, split it into smaller modules

### Component Structure
- One main component per file
- Always define TypeScript interfaces for props
- Use named exports for components
- Use 'use client' directive only when necessary

### Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (UserProfile.tsx)
- Hooks: camelCase with 'use' prefix (useAuth.ts)
- Utils: camelCase (formatDate.ts)
- Constants: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE (MAX_FILE_SIZE)

### Import Order
1. React/Next imports
2. Third-party imports
3. Internal imports (absolute paths with @/)
4. Types
5. Styles

### Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS exclusively
- Use cn() utility for conditional classes
- Support both light and dark modes
- Use CSS variables for theming

### Internationalization
- All user-facing text must be translated
- Use useTranslations() hook
- Support at minimum: English (en), German (de)

### TypeScript
- Strict mode enabled
- No 'any' types
- Use interfaces over types for objects
- Always type function parameters and returns

### Testing
- Components should be testable
- Avoid side effects in render

### Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML
- Include aria labels where needed
- Ensure keyboard navigation works

## Code Quality Checklist
- [ ] No linter errors
- [ ] No TypeScript errors
- [ ] File under 300 lines
- [ ] Props interface defined
- [ ] Translations added
- [ ] Dark mode works
- [ ] Mobile responsive

## Folder Structure
```
app/           - Next.js App Router pages
components/    - React components by feature
lib/           - Utilities, hooks, services
types/         - TypeScript definitions
database/      - Database schema
```

## Component Template
```tsx
/**
 * ComponentName
 * Brief description.
 */

import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';

interface ComponentNameProps {
  propName: string;
  className?: string;
}

export function ComponentName({ propName, className }: ComponentNameProps) {
  return (
    <div className={cn('base-styles', className)}>
      {/* JSX */}
    </div>
  );
}
```

